[SN]TITLE[SN]
East Belfast shop staff threatened with crossbow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A robber armed with a crossbow has threatened staff at a shop in east Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He entered the shop on the Newtownards Road, close to the Dee Street junction, shortly before 09:10 BST on Saturday.
He threatened staff and escaped with cash.  Police said the workers were not injured during the robbery.
The suspect was wearing a camouflage jacket, blue jeans and trainers and detectives have appealed for witnesses.
